<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 03 at 6:32PM MDT until August 03 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 700 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN WELD AND NORTHWESTERN LOGAN COUNTIES...
At 632 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Westplains, or
23 miles northwest of Sterling, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated. At 615 PM MDT, a storm chaser reported
half dollar size hail north of Stoneham.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. Hail damage to
vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Westplains.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
